\par 
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af13\loch\f1 [Dirac Blade]
\par 
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af13\loch\f1 Found: Weapons depot
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af13\loch\f1 An experimental weapon, its energy blade can slice through most enemies with ease, including ethereals. It is capable of destroying certain walls and objects, revealing new paths to take. Its only \hich\af1\dbch\af13\loch\f1 
disadvantage is its relatively short range, and constant use can drain its energy reserves. (Might be needed for balance?)
\par 
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af13\loch\f1 [Sword of Damocles]
\par 
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af13\loch\f1 Found: Undetermined
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af13\loch\f1 A living extension of her own arm, which Tabby can use to suck the life out of anything liv\hich\af1\dbch\af13\loch\f1 
ing and add it to her own, usually killing them instantly unless they are particularily strong. Does average damage to ethereal enemies, but cannot steal life from them. Ineffective against machines. Killing enough enemies charges up the sword's blood met
\hich\af1\dbch\af13\loch\f1 e\hich\af1\dbch\af13\loch\f1 r, and when it is full, Tabby can perform a super powerful attack. (Dunno what yet)
\par 
